author: Reuters Editorial
title: Ireland extends coronavirus lockdown until May 5
description: Ireland on Friday extended stay-at-home restrictions designed to slow the spread of coronavirus until May 5, Prime Minister Leo Varadkar said.
content:
DUBLIN (Reuters) - Ireland on Friday extended stay-at-home restrictions designed to slow the spread of coronavirus until May 5, Prime Minister Leo Varadkar said.
